abstract_ssm: Kenneth S. Wyatt (1900-1967) was a research engineer who worked to develop extra-high voltage cables, capable of insulating 500,000 volts.  His papers contain articles, drafts, technical reports, conference proceedings, photographs, blueprints, and product samples.
